<plot>A psychiatrist (Paul Michael Glaser) treats his patients - sufferers from agoraphobia, claustrophobia, acrophobia, a fear of snakes, and a fear of man - with radical therapy in which they confront their fears by watching them on a large screen. The result is that each patient is driven to commit violent acts, and each dies by what he most fears.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?431278</url></doc>
